273
00:12:06,390 --> 00:12:10,060
I was watching a DVD.

274
00:12:10,150 --> 00:12:11,460
Let me remind you again.

275
00:12:12,150 --> 00:12:14,490
Falsification of evidence is also a crime.

276
00:12:15,300 --> 00:12:16,180
No,

277
00:12:16,420 --> 00:12:17,300
OK

278
00:12:17,680 --> 00:12:18,670
Then I'll ask you again.

279
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:20,680
At the time of the crime,

280
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:22,630
what is the plot of the movie about?

281
00:12:24,210 --> 00:12:27,340
Evan was saying goodbye to Judy.

282
00:12:31,730 --> 00:12:33,460
You can stop your show now.

283
00:12:33,830 --> 00:12:34,740
At first, you said

284
00:12:34,830 --> 00:12:37,050
you didn't know anything because
you were watching TV at home.

285
00:12:37,430 --> 00:12:38,810
But when I told you about
the condition of off-line.

286
00:12:38,900 --> 00:12:40,980
You told me you were watching a DVD again.

287
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:42,220
And when I asked

288
00:12:42,310 --> 00:12:44,060
contents of the film at
the time of the murder.

289
00:12:44,350 --> 00:12:45,480
You can speak out

290
00:12:45,570 --> 00:12:46,670
